Preheat your oven to 240°C/220°C fan/gas mark 9.

Heat a #medium frying pan{} on medium-high heat (no oil).

Once hot, add the @diced chorizo{90%g} and @British beef mince{240%g} and fry until
browned, ~{5-6%minutes}. Use a #spoon{} to break it up as it cooks, then drain and
discard any excess fat.

Season with @salt{} and @pepper{}. IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after
handling raw mince. It's cooked when no longer pink in the middle.

While the beef cooks, peel and grate the @garlic cloves{2} (or use a #garlic press{}).
Grate the @mature cheddar cheese{60%g}.

Once the beef is browned, add the garlic, @Central American style spice mix{1%sachet}
and @tomato puree{30%g}. Stir-fry for ~{1%minute}.

Stir in the @water{75%ml} and cook until thickened, ~{2-3%minutes}.

Once thickened, remove from the heat and stir in the @BBQ sauce{32%g}. Taste and
season with salt and pepper if needed.

== Quesadillas ==

Lay the @plain taco tortillas{4} (2 per person) onto a lightly oiled #baking tray{}
and spoon the beef filling onto one half of each one.

Top with the cheese, then fold the other side over to make a semi-circle. Press down
to keep together.

Rub a little @olive oil{for brushing} over the top of each one.

Bake your quesadillas on the top shelf of your oven until golden, ~{5-7%minutes}.

== Baby Leaf Salad ==

While the quesadillas bake, pop the @cider vinegar{15%ml} and @olive oil{1%tbsp}
for the dressing into a large #bowl{}.

Season with salt and pepper, then mix together.

Just before serving, add the @baby leaf mix{50%g} to the bowl of dressing and toss
to coat.

When ready, share the BBQ beef quesadillas between your plates.

Serve with the salad alongside. Enjoy!